fileChanges.details:
Extract $alt from attributes. In the wp_get_attachment_image call, conditionally include 'alt' in the attributes array: if $alt is non-empty, use it; otherwise omit the 'alt' key so WordPress falls back to the media library alt text. This ensures author-provided alt text takes precedence.

Code change in the wp_get_attachment_image call:
$img_attrs = [
  'class' => 'w-full h-full object-cover absolute inset-0',
  'style' => 'object-position: ' . theme_image_position( $image['focalPoint'] ) . ';',
];
$alt = $attributes['alt'] ?? '';
if ( $alt !== '' ) {
  $img_attrs['alt'] = $alt;
}
echo wp_get_attachment_image( $image['id'], 'full', false, $img_attrs );

In the useInnerBlocksProps call, add role: 'list' to the first argument object (the wrapper props). This ensures the editor matches the frontend semantics.

Change the first argument from:
{ className: className({...}) }
To:
{ className: className({...}), role: 'list' }
